Only my mother's. Only my mother's. And - later on in life I went to the City Hospital to be a nurse for three months probation and I saw my second dead person, when I was over twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8851753 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16741939\charrsid3622924 Who attended your mother's funeral?
